<main id="transport">
    The transport layer of the internet is the mechanism by which applications on different hosts communicate. 
    To do this, they typically will employ two of the protocols available at this layer: TCP and UDP.

    <h2>UDP</h2>
    <p>
        <abbr title="User Datagram Protocol">UDP</abbr> is a simple protocol that offers applications nothing but the bare mininum to establish a connection. 
        UDP is considered to be <em>connectionless</em> because all packets it sends are considered to be independent and not part of a flow of related packets. 
        UDP is also an <em>unreliable</em> protocol; it makes no guarantees of delivery to the applications that use it.
    </p>

